ibution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a Latin byname meaning ‘great’, this was first extracted from the name of <i>Charlemagne</i> (recorded in Latin chronicles as <i>Carolus Magnus</i> ‘Charles the Great’) and used as a given name by the Scandinavians. It was borne by seven medieval kings of Norway, including  Magnus I  (  1024–47 ), known as Magnus the Good, and  Magnus VI  (  1238–80 ), known as Magnus the Law Mender. There are several early Scandinavian saints called Magnus, including an earl of  Orkney  (  d. 1116 ), to whom Kirkwall cathedral is dedicated. The name was imported to Scotland and Ireland during the Middle Ages."],"variants":[{"name":"Mànas","meanings":["Gaelic equivalent of   Magnus ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Magnus de Heaton I married Mrs. Magnus de Heaton before 1108. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1115–1180":"1115–1180","–Male":"Surnud","1115":"1115","before 1108":"enne 1108","1180":"1180","Mersham, Grimsargh, Lancashire, England":"Grimsargh, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1115–1180":"1115–1180","–Male":"Kuollut","1115":"1115","before 1108":"ennen vuotta 1108","1180":"1180","Mersham, Grimsargh, Lancashire, England":"Grimsargh, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1115–1180":"1115–1180","–Male":"Décédé","1115":"1115","before 1108":"avant 1108","1180":"1180","Mersham, Grimsargh, Lancashire, England":"Grimsargh, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Magnus de Heaton I a épousé Mrs. Magnus de Heaton avant 1108. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1115–1180":"1115–1180","–Male":"Verstorben","1115":"1115","before 1108":"vor 1108","1180":"1180","Mersham, Grimsargh, Lancashire, England":"Grimsargh, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Magnus de Heaton I hat vor 